/* new for v5.0 */
@3000016  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I gave the dwarven journal to Draglon who in the Undercellars, and I fear I have lost my way to contact the other mentioned dwarf, Wostok, who the journal was actually meant for. Maybe there is still a way to ask for him in the temple of Helm in Baldur's Gate if I have more insight into this cult "Serpents of Abbathor".~
@3000017  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I met a dwarf in the Undercellar who greeted me as a <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>, but what it is about he wouldn't tell me and instead left with a threat about a powerful enemy I made... I wished people wouldn't be so thin-skinned. Maybe I'll learn more about what he meant - my gut is telling me that I will need a dwarf in my group to find such information.~
@3000018  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I showed Bashrik's journal to Draglon, the contact of the Serpents of Abbathor, but he didn't like how I asked for more information and left with a threat about a powerful enemy I made... I guess my best bet to get more information about this is to go and look for this Wostok inside the temple of Helm in Baldur's Gate.~
@3000019  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I confronted Draglon, the contact of the Serpents of Abbathor, but he didn't like how I asked for more information and left with a threat about a powerful enemy I made... I guess my best bet to get more information about this is to go around with the cult pamphlet and see whether anyone knows something about it.~
