@3000026  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

Sigh - I made an enemy out of *another* evil organization who thought I'd play the henchman for them. I guess they are dangerous enough but we'll see whether they'll send more than one group of assassins after me if they realize I might be dangerous, myself.~
@3000027  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I agreed to kill Wostok and his comrades for Draglon, the contact of the Serpents of Abbathor. Wostok was last seen in the Temple of Helm in Baldur's Gate. When I'm done, I will find Draglon again in the Undercellars.~ 
@3000028  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

Wostok is dead.~
@3000029  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

A mage named Jenna keeps an artifact for the dwarves. She and her companion Jassir reside in the Northwestern District's tavern. I need to go there and retrieve the ancient dwarvern artifact from them.~
@3000030  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I have the Gundmagtor, the dwarven artifact Draglon wanted me to retrieve. I should return to the undercellars and give it to him.~
@3000031  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

Draglon gave me a key to a warehouse in south east Baldur's Gate where the Serpents of Abbathor have a meeting. I am invited and should join with them to discuss my further affiliation to the cult.~
@3000032  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I'll find Wostok who can give me answers to the Serpents of Abbathor in the sewers.~
/* former @3000007 with more details */
@3000033  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I witnessed an ambush at the Coast Way and found a journal from a dwarf named Bashrik. It mentions two fractions: Draglon from the Serpents of Abbathor, a cult who worship an evil dwarven god, and Wostok who was investigating the cult. Wostok was supposed to meet with Bashrik in the Temple of Helm in Baldur's Gate. Draglon from the cult was last seen in the Undercellar.~
@3000034  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I didn't agree to help Wostok further against the Serpents of Abbathor, but I think I could still check out this Draglon from the cult in the Undercellars if I feel like it.~
@3000035  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I should go to the the temple of Helm in Baldur's Gate again to meet Wostok.~
/* @3000012 with more info */
@3000036  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

Jenna was killed by the Serpent's minions, and the artefact was taken. I should return to Wostock in the temple of Helm in Baldur's Gate and tell him about it!~
@3000037  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

We granted Wostok's plea to die by our hand - I would lie if I said we fulfilled his request without emotions. I hope he and his friends are now in whatever afterlife they were wishing for.~
@3000038  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

Wostok plead to die by our hand instead of waiting for his wounds to take him. Never would I have thought that this would be our last act of help we would need to do for him.~

@3000050  = ~Wostok

I should bring Wostok's body to the temple in Helm in Baldur's Gate. I am sure the priest knows how to get him to his clan.~
@3000051  = ~Wostok

I brought Wostok to the priest of Helm. He will see to his and his friends' bodies being transferred to his clan for a proper burial.~
@3000052  = ~Wostok~

@3000054  = ~What to do with the Gundmagtor?~
@3000055  = ~What to do with the Gundmagtor?

The Gundmagtor, an ancient, evil dwarven artefact which I have no use for is now in my possession. Question is what I will do with it now. Keeping it seems pointless - maybe there are better people than an evil dwarf cult interested in it? Wostok's friends for example - the priest in the temple of Helm in Baldur's Gate should know about it. Or I could show it to mages who are used to handling powerful artefacts - destroying this thing so noone else can misuse it would be a valid option, too.~
@3000056  = ~What to do with the Gundmagtor?

The Gundmagtor, an ancient, evil dwarven artefact which I have no use for is now in my possession. Question is what I will do with it now. Keeping it seems pointless - I could show it to mages used to handling powerful artefacts.~
@3000057  = ~What to do with the Gundmagtor?

I gave the Gundmagtor, the ancient evil dwarven artefact to the priest of Helm. He will transfer it to Wostok's friends - I am sure they'll know what to do with it so it won't cause harm ever again.~
@3000058  = ~What to do with the Gundmagtor?

I sold the Gundmagtor, the ancient evil dwarven artefact to an emissary of the Zhentarim for a nice sum of gold.~
@3000059  = ~What to do with the Gundmagtor?

An emissary of the Zhentarim offered me to buy the dwarven artefact Gundmagtor. He sounded very determined to obtain the artefact. I can find him in the Blushing Mermaid.~
@3000060  = ~What to do with the Gundmagtor?

I gave the Gundmagtor, the ancient evil dwarven artefact to Thalantyr in High Hedge. He will destroy it. This cost me 1000 gold, so I hope he does it thoroughly!~
@3000061  = ~What to do with the Gundmagtor?

Thalantyr, the mage in High Hedge, offered to destroy the dwarven artefact Gundmagtor. He wants 1000 gold as compensation for the expenses!~
@3000062  = ~What to do with the Gundmagtor?

Well, Halbazzer Drin is no help here. He flat out rejected to even look at the Gundmagtor further.~

/* BG2 follow up for good path */
@3000080  = ~A friendly Dwarf

I was approached by a dwarf who said that he is a messenger from someone who needs my services. I'll find them in the Copper Coronet in the Slums of Athkatla.~
@3000081  = ~A friendly Dwarf

Would you look at that - the dwarf who approached me was one of two good friends of Wostok, the dwarven warrior and priest I assisted against the evil dwarven cult "Serpents of Abbathor" lead by Lugosch, who I drove out of the Nashkel mines. How could I forget brave Wostok who's last wish was to rather die by my hand than wait for his wounds to take him... They gave me his hammer, a mighty weapon by the looks of it, and asked me to tell of Wostok's bravery whenever anyone asks about this weapon.~
@3000082  = ~A friendly Dwarf~
@3000083  = ~Cromwell can enchant Wostok's hammer so I can throw him, too! For that, he'd need a scroll of Enchanted Weapon, a scroll of Melf's Minute Meteors, and a Diamond, and probably a sum of gold he didn't specify yet.~
@3000084  = ~Cespenar can upgrade Wostok's hammer with a hammer +2 and 10,000 gold.~
@3000085  = ~Cespenar can upgrade Wostok's hammer with a hammer +2, a scroll of Enchanted Weapon, a diamond, and 10,000 gold.~
@3000086  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I have a strong feeling that I will need a dwarf in my group to receive such information..~


